<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03096h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03096h">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03096h"> 96(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Faraway Isles</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> &ldquo;A certain trustworthy monk&rdquo; told <font color="green">[Diciul the Geographer]</font> of the existence of <mark>the Faroe Islands</mark>, and how he had reached them by sailing for two summer days and one summer night in a vessel with two benches of rowers, and discovered that for almost a century there had dwelt on these islands hermits from Ireland. <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 103</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
